definition: (of a smell) strong/peak season (of a crop)/(classifier for the ordinal number of a crop, in the context of multiple harvests)
gas/air/smell/weather/to make angry/to annoy/to get angry/vital energy/qi

sentences.english: Another flight of jets exploded through sound .
sentences.chinese: 又一隊噴氣機雷鳴般地突破了音障。

sentences.english: At one point the company bought from Nippon Airways a 727 jet.
sentences.chinese: 有一次公司從日本航空公司買了一架727型噴氣機。

sentences.english: An aircraft takeoffaided by an auxiliary jet or rocket.
sentences.chinese: 助飛用噴氣機或火箭幫助航空器起飛。

sentences.english: They are going to put a new jet into service on the new year's day.
sentences.chinese: 他們準備在新年第一天把一架心的噴氣機投入使用。

sentences.english: They will use magnetic forces or jet engines and they will ride on air.
sentences.chinese: 他們會利用磁力或噴氣機，他們會在空氣上行駛。

sentences.english: A jet planed in from the south.
sentences.chinese: 一架噴氣機從南面飛來。

sentences.english: Jet A/C is training for acrobatics FLT at 6000m.
sentences.chinese: 噴氣機在特技飛行訓練，高度6000米。
許多噴氣機都有加力燃燒室。
噴氣機每天飛經那個地區。
噴氣機確實在射程以內。

sentences.english: Artest compared joining the Jets to taking a pay cut to play for the Lakers two years ago.
sentences.chinese: 阿泰斯特將加盟噴氣機隊比作兩年前降薪加盟湖人。

sentences.english: Jet was also an efficient bug-zapper and a terrific "watchdog."
sentences.chinese: “噴氣機”還是個滅蟲能手和出色的“看家狗”。

sentences.english: Make sure that the air jet tubes do not protrude from the grid face.
sentences.chinese: 切記空氣噴氣機管不從柵格面孔推出。

sentences.english: Eagles may soar, but weasels don't get sucked into jet engines.
sentences.chinese: 雄鷹可以翱翔，但黃鼠狼不會被吸到噴氣機引擎裏。

sentences.english: Replace the air jets tubes if necessary.
sentences.chinese: 如果需要，替換空氣噴氣機管。

sentences.english: Jet assumed many roles as a member of our family.
sentences.chinese: 身爲家庭一員，“噴氣機”扮演多個角色。
